1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,760
You're the one
who ordered Chin Seng's death, aren't you?

2
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,760
There's been an order from above.

3
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,479
- By whom?
- Phraya…

4
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,800
There must be something
hidden behind all this.

5
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:13,880
The name just came out.

6
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:18,280
You don't see me
as your master anymore, do you?

7
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,000
Duangjai.

8
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,840
We split up here.

9
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:31,160
Look at this.
By now, your face must be everywhere.

10
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,000
Yiam, don't.

11
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,520
Extinguish the three fires…

12
00:02:56,840 --> 00:03:01,040
Let go. Accept. Be calm.

13
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,840
Yiam, calm your mind.

14
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:09,120
Now that you've seen my father,
let's talk first.

15
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,800
I won't talk!

16
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,640
Yiam.

17
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:13,680
Hey.

18
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,840
Stop right now.

19
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:18,320
You are a righteous man,
that is why you can wield the Lek Lai.

20
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,640
But never use a sacred power for evil.

21
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,040
Or it will turn against you.

22
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:28,440
Listen.
We were your father's sworn brothers.

23
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,760
<i>Ma!</i>

24
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,400
<i>A!</i>

25
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,480
<i>U!</i>

26
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,520
Yiam, don't!

27
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:51,040
Lek Lai exists to punish evil,
not to avenge.

28
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,000
Or its power will turn on you.

29
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:57,480
I'd rather die!
I'll die right here with you!

30
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,560
Yiam, don't.

31
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,200
Ah!

32
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,920
- Yiam!
- Yiwha!

33
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:26,640
Yiam! Yiam!

34
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,560
Yiam!

35
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,560
Yiam!

36
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:03,640
Damn it. I never thought
Yod's son would meet such an end.

37
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,400
Yeah.

38
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:09,360
Who knows what karma Yod committed…

39
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,640
In this life or any other,
Yod only did good deeds.

40
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:18,840
What happened to his family

41
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:23,040
was the work of evil men. I regret…

42
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:28,120
I regret that Yiam died

43
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:32,120
still misunderstanding
that I killed his father.

44
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,760
So where should we hide Yiwha now?

45
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,720
Yiwha…

46
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,600
Yiwha.

47
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,280
Yiam…

48
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,680
I love you.

49
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,560
I'll remember your smile today
until the day I die, Orror.

50
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,080
I told you I love you,

51
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:29,000
but you still haven't answered me.
Do you love me?

52
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,880
I love you.

53
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,040
Hearing you say you love me…

54
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:41,240
Even if I died, I wouldn't regret my life.

55
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,080
I loved you…

56
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:55,280
and I have no regrets either…

57
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,840
- Yiwha!
- Dad!

58
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:13,960
Let go!

59
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,680
Yiwha, don't.

60
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,920
- Let go!
- Don't.

61
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,920
Yiwha.

62
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,960
How can you leave me like this?

63
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,240
Yiwha.

64
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:34,120
You still have me.

65
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:36,800
Do you hear me?

66
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:39,680
You still have me.

67
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,160
Dad…

68
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,680
I loved Yiam.

69
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,600
I know.

70
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,840
Your time's up, Pae.

71
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:28,960
I told you I'm not ready to talk yet.

72
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:33,679
All of you, get out.

73
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,280
Get out!

74
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:45,520
Confess everything.

75
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,440
Say it!

76
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,960
You want to die that badly?
I'll send you off myself.

77
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:12,080
Fine! I'll talk!

78
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,520
Tycoon Thongyoo

79
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:21,240
ordered the murders
of Chin Seng and Chin Yuan.

80
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:26,960
And was it you?

81
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,920
Was it you who shot my dad?

82
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:45,400
If you already know, why ask?

83
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,680
Pae,

84
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,480
you shot my dad!

85
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,800
You killed my dad!

86
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:55,240
- Don't!
- Let go of me!

87
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,920
Help me!

88
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,640
- Pun!
- You killed my dad!

89
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,600
- Let go of me!
- Pun, stop.

90
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:15,600
Pun.

91
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,120
You're a policeman.

92
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,320
You can't act like a vigilante.

93
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:23,080
We already have his confession.

94
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,600
Send him to the provincial patrol.

95
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,280
He'll face the death sentence for sure.

96
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:32,080
Right now, you should
go deal with the mastermind first.

97
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,520
Thongyoo.

98
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,560
Chang. Chang.

99
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:47,320
Chang, I have something to ask.

100
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:30,240
So? What are those damn police doing?

101
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:33,800
Pun's still turning the place upside down
looking for you, boss.

102
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,880
And he'll come up empty like always.

103
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,080
No matter what,

104
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:42,320
there's no way I'm letting him catch me.

105
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:47,200
I think we should leave Tha Khiri.

106
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,640
All my land

107
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:54,800
and wealth are in Tha Khiri.

108
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,760
I'm not running.

109
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:01,400
But Phraya Dechanurak is dead now.

110
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:05,040
That's why I'm here.

111
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:08,040
I'll wait until the new governor arrives.

112
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:11,120
- And how do we know that--
- How do we know

113
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:15,680
the new governor
can protect me, is that it?

114
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:20,120
A hundred percent of those governors,

115
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:23,960
their mouths always say
they'll keep the people

116
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,880
safe and happy. But in the end,

117
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:31,640
do you know where their happiness is?

118
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,560
It's in money.

119
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:36,280
And I'll use my money

120
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:39,760
to buy everything back, every last thing.

121
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,440
Pa.

122
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:13,240
I'm useless.

123
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:17,040
I'm an unfilial son.

124
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:32,920
I couldn't save you.

125
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,160
I deserve to die.

126
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:41,280
Pun! Pun!

127
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:45,040
Pun, stop! Don't do this!

128
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:47,080
- Stop!
- Dad.

129
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,360
- I said stop.
- Dad.

130
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,800
Pun!

131
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:51,840
Pun.

132
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,520
Dad…

133
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,520
Pun.

134
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:08,240
Let me die.

135
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,440
Pun, don't.

136
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,320
Enough.

137
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:24,320
Does it hurt?

138
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,360
Pun…

139
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:35,280
Please say something.

140
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,800
What am I supposed to say?

141
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,680
I'm worthless.

142
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,400
I couldn't even avenge Dad.

143
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:49,240
But you caught Pae.

144
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:52,480
He's just a lackey.

145
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:57,120
Thongyoo is still free,
and I can't catch him.

146
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,200
If I die now,

147
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,960
how am I supposed to face Pa?

148
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:17,920
Noree…

149
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:23,120
Noree, why are you crying?

150
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,480
I don't want to hear you talk about dying.

151
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,640
I'm scared.

152
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,320
Scared I'll lose you too.

153
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:41,960
Don't give up yet.

154
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,200
You need to keep fighting.

155
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:47,680
Good has to defeat evil.

156
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,480
Keep fighting. Please.

157
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,560
Don't cry.

158
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:16,360
Don't leave me.

159
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,360
If I don't see your body,

160
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,880
I won't believe you're dead.

161
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:02,960
Yiam.

162
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:05,960
Yiam.

163
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,560
We've stationed people at the pier,

164
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:25,280
but there's still no sign of him.
That means he hasn't fled yet.

165
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:32,800
Alright. That's it for today.
Hold positions exactly as agreed.

166
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,480
What are you planning to do?

167
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,600
I'll catch Thongyoo.

168
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,040
Your hands are meant to hold
a brush and an abacus,

169
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,920
not knives and guns.

170
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:01,280
When the people with guns and power

171
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:03,320
can't punish evil,

172
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,720
then I'll stand up and do it myself.

173
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,600
You gather thugs like this,

174
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:12,880
and the authorities can accuse you
of forming a triad.

175
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,840
The sentence is death.

176
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:22,040
Whatever you're doing, stop it.

177
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:27,640
I'm begging you.

178
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,280
I have to do it.

179
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,840
I dream about Pa every night.

180
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:48,320
He was in agony before he died.

181
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,480
I dream about it again and again.

182
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,840
He suffered so much.

183
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:09,720
Talong.

184
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:14,680
I'm fine.

185
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:19,160
Talong.

186
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:22,080
Talong.

187
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,600
I'm not dead.

188
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,800
My heart is still beating.

189
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:50,480
You weren't moving at all.

190
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,840
Of course I was scared.

191
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:58,280
I should go get Doctor Hong.

192
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,640
I'm better now.

193
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,520
This is what you call better?

194
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:17,240
I'm really better.

195
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,560
And right now,

196
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:25,320
I'm even better than before.

197
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,560
Talong…

198
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:32,120
Don't do something that big.

199
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,320
Cancel your plan.

200
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:39,040
You still have me. You have Pun.

201
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:42,120
But three people

202
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,000
aren't enough.

203
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,000
I'm not done talking yet.

204
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:50,640
You still have my dad,

205
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:53,880
Uncle Niem, Uncle Wad.

206
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:56,600
Everyone is a disciple of Khao Phrom.

207
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:58,800
Once we regroup and steady ourselves,

208
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:01,080
no enemy can defeat us.

209
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,760
Hang in there a little longer.

210
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:32,440
I am hanging in there.
When will I get to rest?

211
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,920
And when are we going to reach the pier?

212
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,520
By tomorrow around noon.

213
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:50,080
Lady Duen.

214
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,240
Lady Duen.

215
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:56,600
Lady Duen.

216
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:01,000
Master?

217
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:05,680
<i>Don't worry. I won't harm your woman.</i>

218
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:09,760
<i>It's time for you to repay me, Lasor.</i>

219
00:22:10,320 --> 00:22:12,920
What do you want me to do, Master?
Just tell me.

220
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:15,920
<i>Go back to Tha Khiri.</i>

221
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:19,480
I can't go back to Tha Khiri.
The police are hunting me.

222
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,920
<i>I told you to go back, so you will.</i>

223
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,880
<i>I've been waiting for this day</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

224
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:29,040
<i>Blood is thicker than water,</i>
<i>is it really true?</i>

225
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:09,360
I'm fine now.

226
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:23,560
This time, I recovered
faster than ever before.

227
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:28,560
Are you sure you're really okay?

228
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:32,200
You possess the most powerful Lek Lai,

229
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,040
it gives you strength, yes.

230
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,000
But if you misuse it,

231
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,520
the punishment

232
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:46,360
can be fatal.

233
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:52,720
That's why I follow
Old Master Khrua Phut's teachings.

234
00:23:56,760 --> 00:24:00,520
From now on, I'll steady my mind,
abandon vengeance,

235
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:05,960
and use the power of Lek Lai
only to deal with evil.

236
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,840
And you will learn the truth

237
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:15,320
that my father is not an evil man.

238
00:25:10,280 --> 00:25:11,400
Stay away from me.

239
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,960
How could I let my wife freeze to death?

240
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:23,560
I'm not your Orror.

241
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,240
And you're not my Blur anymore either.

242
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,080
We don't know what tomorrow will bring.

243
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:42,160
Time is running out for you and me.

244
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:48,360
Tonight, can I be your Blur again,

245
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:50,240
Orror?

246
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,920
Just for this one night.

247
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,000
<i>Yiwha…</i>

248
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:02,960
<i>Yiwha…</i>

249
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:09,600
- Dad.
- So you're here.

250
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:20,360
Yiam. Yiam.

251
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:25,760
Dad, run.

252
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:27,920
Yiam.

253
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:29,920
Listen to me.

254
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:33,440
I swear on my life. I didn't kill Yod.

255
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:37,640
I won't listen to the oath
of a wicked bandit like you.

256
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:51,400
Yiam, don't do anything foolish.

257
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:53,200
Do you want to die?

258
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:55,240
You're the one who must die, Bandit Wad.

259
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,960
I can control Lek Lai now.

260
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:00,560
Don't, Yiam.

261
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,640
<i>Ma, A, U.</i>

262
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:10,120
Dad.

263
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:14,720
Dad!

264
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:17,360
Dad!

265
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:19,560
Dad!

266
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:22,120
Dad!

267
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:49,480
You're about to fully control Lek Lai.

268
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:52,320
I have to warn my dad.

269
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:59,800
Our time is up now.

270
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:29,760
Yiwha?

271
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:41,440
I'LL FIND OUT THE TRUTH ABOUT EVERYTHING.

272
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:50,080
Hey.

273
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:51,840
How is it?

274
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:58,720
We searched all night until dawn
and still haven't found her.

275
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:00,800
Don't lose hope, Wad.

276
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:04,160
I think Yiwha is still
somewhere in this forest.

277
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:07,960
But what's strange is that
we haven't found Yiam's body either.

278
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:13,160
- I'm afraid.
- Afraid of what?

279
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:17,840
Afraid that Yiwha might…

280
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:20,680
Hey, Yiwha wouldn't do anything foolish.

281
00:30:25,520 --> 00:30:27,000
Go take care of what you need to do.

282
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:30,480
Niem and I will handle Yiwha.

283
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:42,520
How is everything? Almost done?

284
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:44,720
Make it shine.
After that, clean upstairs too.

285
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,120
Hurry up.

286
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:49,240
The governor is arriving.

287
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:52,720
That water is filthy. Go change it.

288
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:53,720
Yes, sir.

289
00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:08,360
- Go.
- If you're done, get out.

290
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,760
Where are you taking me?

291
00:31:16,120 --> 00:31:18,360
I'm taking you and all the prisoners

292
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,680
to stand trial
at the Provincial Patrol Department.

293
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:24,800
So you're taking me to my death?

294
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:27,480
Pun,

295
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:29,200
give me one chance, please.

296
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:30,720
- Pun.
- Go!

297
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:34,120
Pun, if I die,

298
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:37,200
you'll never know
how Khun Yod really died.

299
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:45,000
I don't believe a single word
from a damned bastard like you.

300
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:47,400
Move!

301
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:49,760
Stop. Take the prisoners
back into their cells.

302
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:51,960
There's an urgent order from the governor.

303
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,600
The governor will personally
reexamine all the cases.

304
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,280
Hurry up. We'll be late
to welcome the governor.

305
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:17,080
Why are there only two men
guarding the prisoners?

306
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:19,640
They're locked in cells.
What's there to worry about?

307
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:22,000
I'll stay here myself.

308
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:25,560
You all go suck up
to the new governor as much as you like.

309
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:27,560
Fine.

310
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:41,760
Bandit Wad!

311
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:46,480
Today I'll kill you,
so my dad can finally rest in peace.

312
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:55,280
Can you stop now?

313
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:58,400
Now tell me everything.

314
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,360
Who was your father?

315
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:03,600
Why do you hate me this much?

316
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:09,000
Pun…

317
00:33:09,080 --> 00:33:10,120
PATROL UNIT

318
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:13,160
I've never been involved
in power struggles

319
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,640
or trade dealings in Tha Khiri.

320
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,240
And people like me

321
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:19,680
don't kill the innocent.

322
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:22,880
But Lasor is definitely involved.

323
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:26,520
Thongyoo ordered him
to kill both my father

324
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,440
and Chin Yuan,
who blocked his path to wealth.

325
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,920
If Lasor truly killed your father,

326
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,680
I'll deal with him myself.

327
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:40,160
I give you my word.

328
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:43,680
You're father and son after all.

329
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:48,680
Lasor tried to climb his way
into becoming the governor's assistant

330
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,840
to cleanse his father's name.

331
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,160
Didn't you benefit from it?

332
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:54,920
GUARDING SCHEDULE

333
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:04,360
Then shoot me,

334
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,120
if you think I won't keep my promise.

335
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:42,960
I broke Chaem and Niem out.

336
00:34:44,199 --> 00:34:46,440
I know
I'm now an enemy of the authorities.

337
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:50,000
It's your duty to arrest me.

338
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:53,560
Right now, I don't even know
who's good or bad anymore.

339
00:34:53,639 --> 00:34:56,800
The new governor suddenly
ordered all proceedings halted,

340
00:34:57,840 --> 00:35:00,720
no transfers, no trials
at the Provincial Patrol Department.

341
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:03,880
He says he'll reexamine everything himself

342
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:06,360
and even ordered personnel transfers.

343
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,840
Reexamine the cases by himself?

344
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,920
The new governor
is clearly consolidating control,

345
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:18,160
purging the police. Those who are guilty

346
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:20,640
may walk free this time.

347
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,200
This is getting strange.

348
00:35:41,440 --> 00:35:42,760
Why are we back here?

349
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:53,720
Lasor.

350
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:56,760
Arrest him. He's a bandit.
How dare you let him set foot here?

351
00:35:58,360 --> 00:36:00,880
Hey? Where are all the police?

352
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:08,200
Throw that woman out too.
She has no right to be here.

353
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:15,440
Sir Lasor is an honored guest
of the governor.

354
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,640
And Lady Duen as well.

355
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:19,880
Sir Lasor?

356
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:23,480
Honored guest? He's a bandit.

357
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:27,040
Enough questions.
Just follow the governor's orders.

358
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,360
Oh, oh.

359
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:30,120
Easy.

360
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:33,880
This way, please, my lady.

361
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,200
Please allow me, sir.

362
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:30,880
Sir Lasor, please meet the governor.

363
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,160
The governor wants to see me?

364
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:36,320
Yes, sir.

365
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:43,880
Wait.

366
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:48,720
Please wait here first, my lady.

367
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:51,120
Sure.

368
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:16,440
Look up.

369
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:31,960
Master.

370
00:38:33,680 --> 00:38:37,360
Phraya Kaipetch, Governor of Tha Khiri.

371
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,040
Petch!

372
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:49,080
Wad.

373
00:38:50,680 --> 00:38:51,640
Dad.

374
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:54,640
Protect the governor!

375
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:55,840
<i>Thamuen ngong ya.</i>

376
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:06,960
You're not dead yet?

377
00:39:12,040 --> 00:39:13,640
What is it, Bandit Wad?

378
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,600
Surprised I'm still alive?

379
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:19,640
Dad, you and Master know each other?

380
00:39:22,120 --> 00:39:23,400
A monster like you

381
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:26,880
should never have been allowed
by Heaven and Earth to live this long.

382
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:30,480
Even if I'm a monster,
I'm not as evil as a father like you.

383
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:34,160
You didn't just try to erase
sorcery from your son,

384
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:37,320
you even tried to wipe Lasor's memories.

385
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:39,400
Let me ask you this.

386
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:41,600
Are you still his father at all?

387
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:47,280
Dad.

388
00:39:50,560 --> 00:39:51,800
Tell me.

389
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,360
Is it true?

390
00:40:04,520 --> 00:40:06,600
It has to hurt so you'll remember.

391
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:08,920
This charm exists to protect you,

392
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,960
not for you to fool around
and test it for fun.

393
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:12,520
Why would you do this?

394
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:14,440
I finally found a way to learn magic.

395
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:17,720
So you'd learn filthy,
cursed magic like this, huh?

396
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:19,800
Ruining yourself isn't enough.

397
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:22,080
<i>You'd drag</i>
<i>everyone else down with you too.</i>

398
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,440
Lasor,

399
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:29,760
your father intended to kill you.

400
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:33,480
And he hates you this much.

401
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:36,240
- And you still call him your father?
- Petch!

402
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:39,480
Today, I'll send you to hell.

403
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:41,720
Dad, if you want to kill my master,

404
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:46,520
- step over my dead body first.
- Lasor! Move!

405
00:40:46,600 --> 00:40:48,600
No. Master loves me

406
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:50,200
more than my own father ever did.

407
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,440
I'll protect him with my life.

408
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:56,400
If you step forward,

409
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:58,000
don't blame me for being ungrateful.

410
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,880
If you think this bastard is so righteous,

411
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,080
don't call yourself my son.

412
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:30,600
Lasor.

413
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:44,920
Fine.

414
00:41:51,720 --> 00:41:53,400
If you don't want me as your son,

415
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:04,120
then I won't be your son anymore.

416
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:12,280
Bandit Wad,

417
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:15,680
if you want my head, come and take it.

418
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:18,800
Don't hesitate. I'm ready anytime.

419
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:41,240
Go after Bandit Wad!

420
00:43:27,680 --> 00:43:31,120
<i>You're the one who sent men</i>
<i>to kill Khun Yod Pakdee</i>

421
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:33,680
and framed my father and brother.

422
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:41,320
There's been an order from above.

423
00:43:43,400 --> 00:43:46,440
I was ordered to kill Khun Yod Pakdee.

424
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:49,880
Anyone who dared
command a governor like Duang

425
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:52,400
can't be ordinary.

426
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:57,480
Who is it?

427
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:06,800
Yiwha.

428
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:09,680
Uncle Niem. Uncle Chaem.

429
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:13,400
Chaem, you're not bad at all,

430
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:15,520
tracking my niece down like this.

431
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:18,320
Where's Dad?

432
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:21,320
There. Speak of the devil.

433
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:23,040
Your dad really is hard to kill.

434
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:25,200
Dad.

435
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:26,760
Yiwha.

436
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:28,640
What happened?

437
00:44:45,480 --> 00:44:47,400
You're still heartbroken
about your father?

438
00:44:54,800 --> 00:44:56,000
I never thought

439
00:44:57,960 --> 00:44:59,760
my father could do
something like this to me.

440
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:03,120
Because when you were born,

441
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:05,560
your mother died.

442
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:08,160
So Bandit Wad hates you.

443
00:45:08,240 --> 00:45:09,720
It's not strange.

444
00:45:11,280 --> 00:45:12,480
No one loves me.

445
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:16,000
Even my own father never loved me.

446
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:20,320
I have no one left now, Master.

447
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:22,680
Lasor,

448
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:25,720
listen to me carefully.

449
00:45:26,960 --> 00:45:28,840
From now on, I'll be your father myself.

450
00:45:37,920 --> 00:45:40,520
Tycoon Thongyoo requests an audience,
Your Excellency.

451
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:55,600
A Nok Phangka dagger.

452
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:58,920
I commissioned craftsmen from Tani

453
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:01,560
to forge it for Your Excellency

454
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:03,560
especially.

455
00:46:07,320 --> 00:46:09,040
- Let me see.
- Of course.

456
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:12,760
They say

457
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:15,280
whoever possesses this dagger

458
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:17,520
will be a man of great prestige

459
00:46:17,600 --> 00:46:20,600
and supreme authority.

460
00:46:20,680 --> 00:46:23,640
None can rival him.

461
00:46:23,720 --> 00:46:24,760
Really?

462
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:30,800
Beautiful.

463
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:37,680
Truly beautiful. I've never seen
anything this exquisite before.

464
00:46:51,960 --> 00:46:55,680
It's sharp. What a pity, the tip is

465
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:57,640
slightly chipped.

466
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,280
Your Excellency,

467
00:47:01,360 --> 00:47:04,040
why did you kill my man?

468
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:06,240
Because he failed the job.

469
00:47:06,320 --> 00:47:10,320
You ordered him to eliminate Chin Seng,
yet Chin Seng survived.

470
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:12,360
Keeping him alive would only
waste good rice, wouldn't it?

471
00:47:12,440 --> 00:47:16,600
Your Excellency,
how did you know about this?

472
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:21,720
If there's something I want to know,
I'll know it.

473
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:26,640
Tim, drag the body out.

474
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:27,600
Yes, sir.

475
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:29,640
- Now.
- Yes, sir.

476
00:47:29,720 --> 00:47:31,520
- Hey, now.
- Yes, sir.

477
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:43,840
Hey.

478
00:47:45,920 --> 00:47:46,760
Yes, sir?

479
00:47:46,840 --> 00:47:48,560
Let this be an example.

480
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:52,520
Anyone who fails at their task,
don't expect

481
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:54,240
a second chance from me.

482
00:48:03,040 --> 00:48:04,240
Petch is still alive.

483
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:05,160
Huh?

484
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:09,440
Who is Petch, Dad?

485
00:48:11,560 --> 00:48:14,000
He was a fellow disciple of Khao Phrom,
trained alongside me,

486
00:48:14,080 --> 00:48:16,320
Yod, Niem, and Chaem.

487
00:48:21,880 --> 00:48:24,920
<i>Ewang me suttang ekang sabbayang</i>

488
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:26,760
<i>bhagava rajagaha</i>

489
00:48:26,840 --> 00:48:28,760
<i>viharati gija bhute</i>

490
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:32,400
<i>babbate atthakho cattaro maharaja…</i>

491
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:50,640
<i>Although Petch entered Khao Phrom</i>
<i>as our fellow disciple,</i>

492
00:48:50,720 --> 00:48:54,080
<i>Old Master Khrua Phut</i>
<i>refused to pass down sorcery</i>

493
00:48:54,160 --> 00:48:56,120
<i>or occult arts to him at all.</i>

494
00:48:58,120 --> 00:49:00,880
Don't be bitter, Petch.

495
00:49:01,760 --> 00:49:03,000
If Master Phut

496
00:49:03,080 --> 00:49:05,840
won't teach you sorcery,

497
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:09,880
come study medicine with me.

498
00:49:09,960 --> 00:49:11,320
I'll teach you.

499
00:49:13,000 --> 00:49:15,160
I want to be a sorcerer,
not a herbal doctor.

500
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:20,760
Master Phut is biased.
He has many disciples.

501
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:23,840
He teaches everyone else
but refuses to teach me.

502
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:27,520
To become a sorcerer,

503
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:32,160
depends on one's fate.

504
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:36,920
He must know you're unfit for that path.

505
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:39,600
That's why he doesn't teach you.

506
00:49:40,200 --> 00:49:42,640
Fine. If he won't teach me, so be it.

507
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:46,480
Because now there's something

508
00:49:46,560 --> 00:49:48,880
I want more than any sorcery.

509
00:49:57,440 --> 00:49:58,800
I heard

510
00:49:59,560 --> 00:50:02,720
you possess a crystal fang
that grows from the roof of your mouth,

511
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:04,280
is that true?

512
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:11,000
Why are you asking me this, Petch?

513
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:15,240
Then I'll ask another question.

514
00:50:16,920 --> 00:50:19,840
If I possess a divine relic
like the crystal fang,

515
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:23,200
I'll surpass every disciple in Khao Phrom,

516
00:50:24,280 --> 00:50:25,160
won't I?

517
00:50:48,520 --> 00:50:50,840
What are you going to do to me, Petch?

518
00:50:58,040 --> 00:51:00,560
Please give me the crystal fang.

519
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:01,560
No.

520
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:12,480
Please give it to me.

521
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:14,960
Open your mouth.

522
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:25,360
My crystal fang.

523
00:51:27,400 --> 00:51:28,800
Master.

524
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:31,640
Petch, what have you done to Master?

525
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:35,000
My crystal fang. My crystal fang.

526
00:51:35,080 --> 00:51:36,520
Petch! You bastard!

527
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:37,760
Hey!

528
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:40,520
- Petch!
- Let go of me!

529
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:41,680
- Ugh!
- Petch!

530
00:51:47,040 --> 00:51:49,440
Let go of me.

531
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:52,520
You killed Old Master Nutat.

532
00:51:52,600 --> 00:51:55,120
You must face punishment
under the laws of Khao Phrom.

533
00:51:59,680 --> 00:52:01,120
Have you all forgotten already?

534
00:52:02,040 --> 00:52:03,880
I have the crystal fang in my stomach.

535
00:52:03,960 --> 00:52:06,080
You can't do anything to me.

536
00:52:06,160 --> 00:52:08,960
Old Master's crystal fang will never
protect a scumbag like you, Petch.

537
00:52:09,640 --> 00:52:12,600
We should kill him. Don't leave him
alive to become a curse upon Khao Phrom.

538
00:52:13,480 --> 00:52:14,520
Niem.

539
00:52:14,600 --> 00:52:16,720
Don't forget the rules of Khao Phrom.

540
00:52:17,920 --> 00:52:19,320
We do not kill our fellow disciples.

541
00:52:23,320 --> 00:52:25,320
We'll wait until
Old Master Khrua Phut returns.

542
00:52:26,920 --> 00:52:28,280
Then we'll decide what to do.

543
00:52:33,520 --> 00:52:34,520
THREE MONTHS LATER

544
00:52:34,600 --> 00:52:36,120
If I survive this,

545
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:38,560
I'll make you all suffer

546
00:52:39,320 --> 00:52:40,560
far worse than I ever have.

547
00:52:46,960 --> 00:52:50,200
Petch killing Old Master Nutat

548
00:52:50,280 --> 00:52:51,640
is a grave sin.

549
00:52:52,280 --> 00:52:54,760
But executing a man, taking a life,

550
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:57,240
is not the duty of a monk like myself.

551
00:52:58,520 --> 00:53:01,880
Then we must hand him over to the courts
and let the executioner

552
00:53:01,960 --> 00:53:03,360
put him to death.

553
00:53:04,240 --> 00:53:06,080
But Petch swallowed the crystal fang.

554
00:53:07,520 --> 00:53:11,480
Even if he's beheaded by an executioner,
he may not die so easily.

555
00:53:13,400 --> 00:53:16,080
Is there any way to resolve this, Master?

556
00:53:16,680 --> 00:53:19,160
The crystal fang is a sacred relic.

557
00:53:20,280 --> 00:53:22,080
To strip Petch of his power,

558
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:24,360
we must perform a cleansing ritual,

559
00:53:24,440 --> 00:53:26,560
remove the crystal fang from his body.

560
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:29,520
Once it no longer protects him,

561
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:32,280
he'll become just an ordinary man.

562
00:53:32,920 --> 00:53:34,400
When shall we begin the ritual?

563
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:37,160
This coming Fifth Saturday.

564
00:53:45,840 --> 00:53:47,280
Make him kneel.

565
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:53,080
You're unjust.

566
00:53:54,960 --> 00:53:58,400
I was your disciple just like them,
yet you refused to teach me any sorcery.

567
00:53:59,560 --> 00:54:02,000
The sorcery of Khao Phrom

568
00:54:02,080 --> 00:54:04,920
is not suited for someone
with a corrupted heart like yours, Petch.

569
00:54:05,640 --> 00:54:09,920
I did this because you forced me to.

570
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:14,160
If you had shown me

571
00:54:14,800 --> 00:54:16,840
the same mercy you gave Wad, Yod,

572
00:54:17,840 --> 00:54:19,680
Chaem, and Niem,

573
00:54:21,480 --> 00:54:24,680
I wouldn't have had to kill
Old Master Nutat.

574
00:54:24,760 --> 00:54:27,800
If you say I'm evil,
then you're even more evil than I am.

575
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:28,800
Petch!

576
00:54:29,640 --> 00:54:30,880
That's enough.

577
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:34,080
Even now, you still haven't realized?

578
00:54:44,560 --> 00:54:46,280
How could I not?

579
00:54:46,360 --> 00:54:49,800
I've realized this world has no justice.

580
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:53,920
Only the weak are bullied.

581
00:54:54,440 --> 00:54:56,480
The strong survive.

582
00:54:58,360 --> 00:55:02,360
Mark my words.

583
00:55:02,440 --> 00:55:04,480
One day, I'll rise to power.

584
00:55:06,640 --> 00:55:08,880
And I'll come back
to take revenge on all of you.

585
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:09,960
All of you!

586
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:16,080
Including you, Old Master Khrua Phut.

587
00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:20,560
- Petch.
- <i>Tiwahi namo buddhaya!</i>

588
00:55:20,640 --> 00:55:22,080
Petch!

589
00:55:22,160 --> 00:55:23,880
Petch.

590
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,520
Hey!

591
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:37,120
Ugh!

592
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:38,600
Hey!

593
00:55:39,840 --> 00:55:40,840
Petch.

594
00:55:45,280 --> 00:55:46,120
Petch!

595
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:14,320
Falling from a cliff that high,
how could he survive?

596
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,600
It must be the power of the crystal fang.

597
00:56:17,680 --> 00:56:19,120
Or someone must have saved him.

598
00:56:19,680 --> 00:56:22,280
Now Petch has become the new
governor of Tha Khiri, replacing Duang.

599
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:27,520
He intends to use Lasor
as a pawn to take revenge on me.

600
00:56:28,880 --> 00:56:31,880
Wait, Dad.
How is Lasor involved in all this?

601
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:36,080
After I drove Lasor out of Chum Suea,

602
00:56:36,840 --> 00:56:39,920
he likely went to study
dark sorcery under Petch.

603
00:56:40,520 --> 00:56:42,080
That's why he calls him Master.

604
00:56:43,800 --> 00:56:46,160
That bastard has always been cold-blooded.

605
00:56:46,240 --> 00:56:49,720
Old Master Nutat was so kind to him,
yet he still killed him.

606
00:56:51,200 --> 00:56:53,760
Lasor, this truly is your karma.

607
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:58,200
So what do we do now?

608
00:57:00,440 --> 00:57:02,520
I'll go bring Lasor back myself.

609
00:57:02,600 --> 00:57:03,680
No.

610
00:57:05,280 --> 00:57:06,880
We'll handle it ourselves.

611
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:13,560
But, Yiwha,

612
00:57:14,520 --> 00:57:16,360
I have something I need your help with.

613
00:57:20,200 --> 00:57:21,400
We've got a situation!

614
00:57:21,480 --> 00:57:22,880
<i>If Pae is dead, that's good.</i>

615
00:57:22,960 --> 00:57:25,000
That's one less enemy for me.

616
00:57:25,080 --> 00:57:26,320
I'll appoint you

617
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:29,120
<i>head of the railway construction unit.</i>

618
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:30,240
Yiam!

619
00:57:30,320 --> 00:57:32,920
<i>Even if it costs me my life,</i>
<i>I have to stop them.</i>

620
00:57:33,000 --> 00:57:34,680
<i>Aren't you afraid</i>
<i>of being charged with rebellion?</i>

621
00:57:34,760 --> 00:57:35,920
What is going on?

622
00:57:36,000 --> 00:57:38,280
How can I destroy
the Lek Lai inside Yiam, Dad?

623
00:57:38,360 --> 00:57:39,560
A woman's menstrual blood.

624
00:57:40,160 --> 00:57:43,600
<i>A woman's menstrual blood carries a curse.</i>
<i>No matter how powerful the sorcery may be,</i>

625
00:57:43,680 --> 00:57:45,600
<i>it will deteriorate.</i>

626
00:57:46,600 --> 00:57:48,640
<i>I suspect he's a master</i>

627
00:57:48,720 --> 00:57:50,040
<i>of dark sorcery.</i>

628
00:57:50,120 --> 00:57:52,760
<i>He might be connected</i>
<i>to the same people who murdered my family.</i>

629
00:57:52,840 --> 00:57:54,600
You're being used.

630
00:58:00,400 --> 00:58:02,000
<i>I'll send all three of you</i>

631
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:05,120
<i>to see Yod in hell!</i>

632
00:58:49,760 --> 00:58:51,480
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
